3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the physical layer parameters required to ensure the system operates below a target peak-age violation probability, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses modulation techniques and channel estimation, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This is the least likely category, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of wireless communication systems.
